The Azure Red Team emulates real-world attacks, providing a critical component of Azure‚Äôs ‚ÄúAssume Breach‚Äù strategy and ensuring readiness against adversaries seeking to compromise the Azure platform. 
We are seeking a who wants to apply their engineering skills to massive-scale attack automation and develop experience in Red Teaming. 
This is a unique position on a unique team. Previous Red Team experience is not required, but engineering acumen, understanding of the cloud, and creativity are must-haves. 
Responsibilities 
Red Team Automation Engineer - You will work on a small team (4 engineers) on building tools that scale and automate Red Team, enabling realistic threat emulation. 
Red Team Operator - You will execute attacks against the Azure platform, which exercise and validate Microsoft‚Äôs ability to prevent, detect, and respond to adversaries. Build your attacker knowledge and automate it! 
Emerging Threat Research ‚Äì You will connect with the community on the forefront of emerging threats which affect online services. This includes research of externally found exploits as well as proactive research on technology the Microsoft Cloud utilizes and depends on. A passion and drive for turning threat intelligence into threat emulation is a must. 
Communication & Presentation ‚Äì You will be a trusted advisor and security expert who partners with and advises service teams on detecting vulnerabilities, reducing attack surface, mitigating threats and implementing security best practices. Present findings through proof-of-concept exploits, white papers, brown bags, filing bugs, presentations and formal reports. Work closely with development teams to define and adopt new solutions for secure development and operations of Microsoft cloud services. 
Qualifications 
Required Qualifications: 
4+ years experience with one or more general purpose programming languages including but not limited to: C#, Python, and data query languages 
BA/BS in an engineering-related discipline or relevant work experience 
Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud background check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter. 
Preferred Qualifications: 
Experience with Red Teaming/Pen Testing 
A strong technical background and solid foundation in software engineering and architecture design 
Experience working on a product with high traffic and many users; live site mentality 
